column5: Looking for any info on Kabenung lake,staying at Normandy lodge sept 15
Sorry I didn't get back to you sooner on WC. I havn't been able to reach the person who has the camp up there.  Sorry.  Hopefully someone else here is familiar with the lake.

the lake can be a great lake.  Make sure you bring your GPS as it is a big lake with lots of bays and fingers and rocks, LOT OF ROCKS!!  The smallmouth bass have exploded and the walleye fishing is still good.  Just be careful that you dont leave your motor on rocks.
4 walleye,6 grouse thats it for 4 days
ive also been looking at normandy lodge hows the pike fishing? and if anyonee knows of any other lodges near wawa hornepayne nakina or shining tree please tell me
